'''Scout Taylor-Compton''' (born '''Desariee Starr Compton''' on [[February 21]], [[1989]] in [[Long Beach, California]]) is an American actress whose film credits include ''[[Love's Unfolding Dream]]'', ''[[An American Crime]]'', ''[[Wicked Little Things]]'', ''[[Tomorrow Is Today (2006 film)|Tomorrow is Today]]'' and ''[[Sleepover (2004 film)|Sleepover]]''.

On the morning of [[August 12]], [[2005]], Taylor-Compton disappeared from her home in [[Apple Valley]], [[California]] and was reported missing after an apparent family disagreement. She was found alive at a friend's house two weeks later, and was declared "a runaway who did not want to be found" by the San Bernardino County Sheriff's office.<ref name="scoutrunaway">[http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0174021/news News for Scout Taylor-Compton] Scout Taylor-Compton - accessed on [[3 January]], [[2007]]</ref> She had dyed her hair black and hid when officers arrived on scene. After speaking with Officer Cesar Molina, she returned to her family.<ref name="scoutrunaway2">[http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/9089736/ Runaway teen actress slept at park] MSNBC.com - [[August 26]], [[2005]]</ref> The news coverage of her disappearance was seen by some as [[Missing_white_woman#Missing_white_females| Missing White Woman]] syndrome.<ref name="scoutrunaway3"> [http://www.americanchronicle.com/articles/viewArticle.asp?articleID=4539 2005 - A Year in Review] Non Stories of 2005: Another white woman goes missing - American Chronicle [[December 31]], [[2005]] </ref>[[Image:Scout-laurie.gif|right|thumb|200 px|Scout as Laurie Strode]]

